    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl>Morelli in <ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>257</citedRange> (ph.)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>104800</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64185"><name nymRef="#Θεύδωρος">Θεύδωρον</name> 
                        <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63860"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Εὐμηλίδας">Εὐμηλίδα</name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-62598"><name nymRef="#Ἀγλωτίμα">Ἀγλωτίμα</name> 
                        <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63097"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἀρίστιππος">Ἀριστίππω</name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="3"/><w lemma="ἀνατίθημι">ἀνέθηκε</w>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Statue de</supplied> Theudôros fils d'Eumèlidas consacrée par Aglôtima fille d'Aristippos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Statue of</supplied> Theudoros son of Eumelidas dedicated by Aglotima daughter of Aristippos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Statua di</supplied> Theudoros figlio di Eumelidas dedicata da Aglotima figlia di Aristippos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>(تمثال) ثيودوروس بن إفميليداس أهدي من قبل أجلوتيما ابنة أريستيبوس</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>A photograph in Archives of the Department of Antiquities at Cyrene (F1837) shows this stone with the mention «<foreign xml:lang="it">nella zona degli altarini</foreign>»,
                    which is exactly the so-called '<foreign xml:lang="it">agorà degli dei</foreign>', West of the Strategeion, where Dobias-Lalou saw it in 1977 and again in 1983. 
                    It may thus be inferred that Morelli's «<foreign xml:lang="grc">Ad est dello Strategeion</foreign>» is a slip of the pen for <foreign xml:lang="it">'ovest'</foreign>. 
                    Besides, the mention on the photograph is a clue for the find dating from the Italian period, before World War II.</p>
	      <p>Aristippa was probably either the wife of the mother of Theudoros.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
